Chilean Stocks: Besalco, La Polar, Andina, Santander, Vapores

-- B y   E d u a r d o   T h o m s o n
-- 
2011-08-01T14:55:44Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-01/chilean-stocks-besalco-la-polar-andina-santander-vapores.html
The following companies are having
unusual price changes in Chilean trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 10:35 a.m. New York time.  The Ipsa index rose 1.1 percent to 4,473.45.  Besalco SA (BESALCO)   climbed 1.3 percent to 765 pesos.
The builder’s second-quarter profit of 2.86 billion pesos ($6.25
million), reported after the close of trading July 29, matched
estimates, brokerage IM Trust wrote in a note to clients today.  Cia. Sudamericana de Vapores SA (VAPORES CC) rose 1 percent
to 274.5 pesos.  Latin America ’s largest container shipping
company forecasts a return to profit in the first quarter of
2012, newspaper La Tercera reported, citing analysts briefed by
the company. Gloria Leiva, an official at Vapores’
communications department, wasn’t immediately available to
comment, an assistant said by telephone.  Corpbanca (CORPBANC)   fell 1.1 to 6.85 pesos. Chile’s
sixth-largest lender by assets was reiterated “underperform”
at Banco Santander SA.  Empresas La Polar SA (LAPOLAR)   rose 4.6 percent to 534
pesos, its third day of gains. The department-store operator
that set aside $900 million in June for consumer-lending losses,
received approval from bondholders July 29 to seek a court
agreement for renegotiating repayments to avoid bankruptcy. The
company also appointed Patricio Lecaros as chief executive
officer, according to a July 29 regulatory filing.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Eduardo Thomson in Santiago at 
